# YTV2 Dashboard Component - Environment Configuration Template
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual values

# ==============================================
# DASHBOARD-ONLY CONFIGURATION
# ==============================================

# IMPORTANT: Leave TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN empty for dashboard-only mode
# This component serves the web interface only
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=""

# Sync secret for secure communication with NAS component (required)
# Generate a secure random string and use the same value on both NAS and dashboard
# This enables secure deletion and file uploads from the NAS component
SYNC_SECRET=your-secure-random-string-here

# ==============================================
# WEB SERVER CONFIGURATION (Render Auto-Configured)
# ==============================================

# Port for the web dashboard (auto-set by Render)
# For local development, use: WEB_PORT=10000
# PORT=10000

# Dashboard URL (auto-set by Render deployment)
# For manual configuration: RENDER_DASHBOARD_URL=https://your-app.onrender.com

# ==============================================
# USAGE INSTRUCTIONS - DASHBOARD COMPONENT
# ==============================================

# This is the DASHBOARD component of the YTV2 hybrid architecture:
# 
# 1. Copy this file: cp .env.template .env
# 2. Generate a secure SYNC_SECRET (same as NAS component)
# 3. Deploy to Render or run locally: python server.py
# 4. Configure NAS component to sync to this dashboard URL
# 5. Access dashboard at your deployment URL
#
# ARCHITECTURE:
# - NAS Component: Telegram bot + YouTube processing + AI summaries
# - Dashboard Component (THIS): Web interface + audio playback + file storage
# - Communication: NAS uploads reports/audio to dashboard via authenticated API

# ==============================================
# SECURITY NOTES
# ==============================================

# - SYNC_SECRET must match between NAS and dashboard components
# - Dashboard accepts uploads only with valid authentication
# - Delete operations require bearer token authentication
# - All communication should use HTTPS in production
